subject: p19890786
Findings: In comparison with the study of, there again are innumerable metastatic nodules involving both lungs with consolidative process involving the right lower lung, associated with pleural effusions. It would be impossible to exclude the possibility of superimposed pneumonia given the extensive underlying lung disease. The known metastatic lesions involving the inferior scapula and nondisplaced fracture of the right posterior eighth rib are not identified on this study.
